From 44bb1bb5c37de7bc87fecb051175ed2dbea6006c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: melnoff <melnoff360@gmail.com>
Date: Sat, 25 Apr 2026 16:36:30 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat(net): VLESS subscription fetcher (Happ:// + base64)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Adds the Phase 2B foundation needed to load servers from a VLESS
subscription:

  * SubscriptionFetcher (QNetworkAccessManager) — accepts a Happ://
    or direct https:// URL, fetches the body, tries plain-text first
    then base64 decode, extracts vless:// lines via ParseVlessUrl,
    emits the resulting QList<VlessParams> over an rpl producer.
  * ResolveSubscriptionUrl() — translates "happ://add/<URL>" or
    "happ://add/<base64-URL>" into the underlying https:// endpoint.
  * BuildSingboxSubscriptionOutboundsJson() — produces the outbounds
    array for sing-box: each subscription server as a "vN" outbound
    plus a "proxy"-tagged urltest selector that picks the fastest.
    The route.final="proxy" wrapper in bridge.go keeps working, so
    a subscription proxy resolves to a single Socks5 with sing-box
    doing internal failover/switching.
  * Minor refactor of vless_parser: BuildSingboxOutboundJson now
    delegates to a private BuildVlessOutboundObject helper that
    takes a custom tag, used by both the single-server and the
    subscription path.

No UI / bridge / persistence wiring yet — those land in patches 10
and 11.
